HEADWORD: passivism
<hw>pas"si*vism`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The doctrine that
all violence is unjustifiable; hence, the principle of passive
resistance.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> pacifism.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quality of being passive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Passivity</ent>⟦br⟧
